pays%20attention%20to%20us%20or%20our%20demands%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sunita%20Pandurang%20Satgir%2C%20carrying%20a%20heavy%20metal%20pot%20on%20her%20head%20filled%20with%20foul-smelling%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemand%20is%20increasing%20in%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20nation%20of%201.4%20billion%20people%2C%20but%20supplies%20are%20shrinking%20--%20with%20climate%20change%20driving%20erratic%20rainfall%20and%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELarge-scale%20infrastructure%20for%20Mumbai%20includes%20reservoirs%20connected%20by%20canals%20and%20pipelines%20channelling%20water%20from%20100%20kilometres%20(60%20miles)%20away.%20But%20experts%20say%20a%20failure%20of%20basic%20planning%20means%20that%20the%20network%20is%20often%20not%20connected%20to%20hundreds%20of%20rural%20villages%20in%20the%20region%20and%20several%20nearby%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20they%20rely%20on%20traditional%20wells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20demand%20far%20outstrips%20meagre%20resources%2C%20and%20critical%20groundwater%20levels%20are%20falling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20days%20and%20our%20lives%20just%20revolve%20around%20thinking%20about%20collecting%20water%2C%20collecting%20it%20once%2C%20and%20collecting%20it%20again%2C%20and%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Satgir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20make%20four%20to%20six%20rounds%20for%20water%20every%20day...%20leaving%20us%20time%20for%20nothing%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeatwaves%20and%20dry%20wells%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20is%20shifting%20weather%20patterns%2C%20bringing%20longer-lasting%20and%20more%20intense%20droughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWells%20rapidly%20run%20dry%20early%20in%20the%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20peak%20of%20summer%2C%2035-year-old%20Satgir%20said%20she%20can%20spend%20up%20to%20six%20hours%20a%20day%20fetching%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETemperatures%20this%20year%20surged%20above%20a%20brutal%2045%20degrees%20Celsius%20(113%20Fahrenheit).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20well%20dries%2C%20the%20village%20then%20relies%20on%20a%20government%20tanker%20with%20irregular%20supplies%2C%20two%20or%20three%20times%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20brings%20untreated%20water%20from%20a%20river%20where%20people%20wash%20and%20animals%20graze.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESatgir's%20home%20in%20the%20dusty%20village%20of%20Navinwadi%2C%20near%20the%20farming%20town%20of%20Shahapur%2C%20lies%20some%20100%20kilometres%20from%20the%20busy%20streets%20of%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20is%20also%20the%20source%20of%20major%20reservoirs%20supplying%20some%2060%20percent%20of%20water%20to%20Mumbai%2C%20local%20government%20authorities%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMumbai%20is%20India's%20second-biggest%20and%20rapidly%20expanding%20city%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%20population%20of%2022%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20that%20water%20from%20around%20us%20goes%20to%20the%20people%20in%20the%20big%20city%20and%20nothing%20has%20changed%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Satgir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20three%20generations%20are%20linked%20to%20that%20one%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20our%20only%20source.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20village%20head%20Rupali%20Bhaskar%20Sadgir%2C%2026%2C%20said%20residents%20were%20often%20sick%20from%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20their%20only%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20requesting%20governments%20for%20years%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20water%20available%20at%20the%20dams%20also%20reaches%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20just%20keeps%20getting%20worse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20authorities%20both%20at%20the%20state%20level%20and%20in%20New%20Delhi%20say%20they%20are%20committed%20to%20tackling%20the%20problem%20and%20have%20announced%20repeated%20schemes%20to%20address%20the%20water%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20villagers%20say%20they%20have%20not%20reached%20them%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Unsustainable%20rates'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20government-run%20NITI%20Aayog%20public%20policy%20centre%20forecasts%20a%20%26quot%3Bsteep%20fall%20of%20around%2040%20percent%20in%20freshwater%20availability%20by%202030%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20July%202023%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20warned%20of%20%26quot%3Bincreasing%20water%20shortages%2C%20depleting%20groundwater%20tables%20and%20deteriorating%20resource%20quality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGroundwater%20resources%20%26quot%3Bare%20being%20depleted%20at%20unsustainable%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added%2C%20noting%20they%20make%20up%20some%2040%20percent%20of%20total%20water%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20story%20repeated%20across%20India%2C%20said%20Himanshu%20Thakkar%2C%20from%20the%20South%20Asia%20Network%20on%20Dams%2C%20Rivers%20and%20People%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20water%20rights%20campaign%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20%26quot%3Btypical%20of%20what%20keeps%20happening%20all%20over%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Thakkar%20said%2C%20adding%20it%20represents%20everything%20%26quot%3Bwrong%20with%20the%20political%20economy%20of%20making%20dams%20in%20India.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20projects%20are%20planned%20and%20justified%20in%20the%20name%20of%20drought-prone%20regions%20and%20its%20people%2C%20most%20end%20up%20serving%20only%20the%20distant%20urban%20areas%20and%20industries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Navinwadi%20village%2C%20residents%20are%20resigned%20to%20living%20on%20the%20strictly%20rationed%20supply.%20When%20the%20water%20tanker%20arrives%2C%20dozens%20of%20women%20and%20children%20sprint%20out%20with%20pots%2C%20pans%2C%20and%20buckets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESantosh%20Trambakh%20Dhonner%2C%2050%2C%20a%20daily%20labourer%2C%20said%20he%20joined%20the%20scr